_source.message:
READ


Good evening everyone,

I received a call from Deputy Secretary of State Chris Beall this afternoon to discuss an issue that occurred with the Eligible But Unregistered (EBU) mailing done by the state per their agreement as a member of ERIC (Electronic Registration Information Center).

This mailing goes to people that ERIC identifies as POTENTIALLY eligible to register to vote, but that are not currently registered. Some information about what ERIC sends to the state and what the mailing includes:
 • The reports include individuals who have a driver’s license/ID card but who are not registered to vote.
 • The data in these reports comes from the DMV, which is protected by the Driver’s Privacy Protection Act of 1993.
 • ERIC does not have political party affiliation data for anyone.
 • States filter out any individuals they know to NOT be eligible.
 • The mailing clearly states the eligibility requirements - age, citizenship, residency, etc.
The state made an error in processing the data from ERIC when attempting to filter out those who are not eligible to register to vote. Unfortunately, this same mistake occurred in 2020 as well. Here is a rundown of the over numbers:
 • ERIC referred approximately 102,000 names of potentially eligible, but not registered people.
 • The state scrubbed the list and sent a mailing to 52,006 people they believed to be eligible but not registered.
Unfortunately, the state has discovered that of the 52,006 mailings sent, approximately 31,000 (60%) of the mailings went to non-citizens. 

The state is working to correct the action in at least the following ways:
 • Sending a new mailing to the approximately 31,000 people to inform them they received the mailing in error and that they are not eligible to register to vote.
 • They will be reviewing the VR list each day to verify that none of those people have registered to vote. If any are currently registered to vote, they will be removed from the list and referred to law enforcement.

A few things to remember about this:
 • This was not a mistake made by ERIC. ERIC continues to be an invaluable tool to help states maintain accurate voter registration lists.
 • A mailing does not equal a voter registration. Upon receiving this mailing, the person would still have to take action to register to vote.
 • If the person tried to register on-line, they would be unable to do so. Non-citizen driver’s licenses have a different data string than citizen driver’s licenses. So OLVR/SCORE would not accept the new non-citizen driver’s license recently implemented.
 • If a person on this list tried to register using a paper form and did not provide their DL, the daily review done by the SOS should catch that occurrence and they will remove that person from the list.
I have asked Chris that they provide a list to each county that includes the overall number of instances per county, along with each name. The state only has the information by zip code, and not county. But Chris is working to get us at least the overall numbers. The SOS is reviewing the request to send us the names as well.

I do expect this to be a topic of conversation on Monday’s Conduct of Elections call. I have requested that the state send additional details via email as well.

There was an article about this on Colorado Public Radio today. Here is a link to the article for your review:

https://www.cpr.org/2022/10/07/colorado-voter-registration-notices-non-citizens/

If you have any questions, please let me know.

Best,

"Scrubs"-Produzent Eric Weinberg wegen Vergewaltigung angeklagt

Der 62-Jährige soll seinen Hollywood-Status benutzt haben, um junge Frauen unter dem Vorwand von Fotoshootings in sein Haus zu locken. Mehr als zwei Dutzend Frauen sollen Übergriffe geschildert haben.

Der Hollywood-Produzent Eric Weinberg, der an Hit-Serien wie "Scrubs" und "Californication" mitgewirkt hat, ist wegen Vergewaltigung und anderen sexuellen Übergriffen angeklagt worden. Gegen den 62-Jährigen liegen Vorwürfe von fünf Frauen vor, die Weinberg zwischen 2014 und 2019 missbraucht haben soll, teilte die Staatsanwaltschaft in Los Angeles am Mittwoch mit.

Der Angeklagte habe seinen Hollywood-Status benutzt, um junge Frauen unter dem Vorwand von Fotoshootings in sein Haus zu locken, wo er sie angeblich missbraucht habe, sagte Staatsanwalt George Gascón. Die Vorwürfe umfassen Vergewaltigung, erzwungenen Oralverkehr und Körperverletzung. Weinberg soll Ende Oktober vor dem Haftrichter erscheinen. Gegen Zahlung einer Kaution von fünf Millionen Dollar kam er zunächst auf freien Fuß. Mehr als zwei Dutzend Frauen hätten in Gesprächen mit dem Hollywood Reporter angebliche Übergriffe von Weinberg geschildert. Die ersten Fälle würden bis ins Jahr 2000 zurückgehen.

https://www.sueddeutsche.de/panorama/scrubs-eric-weinberg-hollywood-produzent-californication-anklage-vergewaltigung-1.5669605

🇺🗽 New York authorities declared a state of emergency in response to an influx of illegal migrants
  
New York City authorities have declared a state of emergency due to an influx of illegal migrants. This was announced by Mayor Eric Adams.  
  
Adams said that since April, at least 17 thousand migrants came to New York. According to him, since September, 5-6 buses with illegals arrived in the city every day, due to which the city's social services have ceased to cope with their tasks.  
  
The mayor said that there are currently more than 60,000 people in the municipal shelter system and 42 additional hotels had to be used to accommodate them. In this case, if the current rate of arrival of refugees in the next year, the number of shelter residents may exceed 100 thousand people.  
  
"Right now we have a situation where more people are arriving in New York than we can immediately accommodate, including families with infants and young children. Once asylum seekers from today's buses are sheltered, we will surpass the highest number of people in the history of our city's shelter system," Adams said during the press conference.  
  
The official separately emphasized that the city needs help from the federal authorities to solve the problems that have arisen. According to Adams, the solution to the migration crisis of this scale will cost $1 billion.  
  
The migration crisis erupted after Mayor Adams declared New York City a "city of refuge" for migrants, whom the authorities of the Republican border states began to expel to the "blue" states.  
  
Republican governors had to resort to such measures after ineffective demands to the Biden administration to secure the southern border of the USA. It is estimated that since late January 2021, when Joe Biden officially took office as President of the United States, more than one million illegal aliens have crossed the United States border.  
  
In turn, representatives of the Democratic Party accused Republicans of an attempt to use refugees as a tool in the political struggle. In particular, this was stated by Eric Adams, who confirmed that New York was ready to accept refugees.  
  
At the same time, many New Yorkers were not delighted with the mayor's idea to host tens of thousands of illegals in the city. Meetings of local residents were held in many neighborhoods, during which they expressed their disagreement with the plans of the municipality to settle refugees in city neighborhoods.  
  
Many citizens were also angered by the fact that migrants receive services from the state that are unavailable to most citizens, including free medical care. Yet not long ago there were rallies in New York City in support of migrants.
